ARV2, 444, no. 241;
                            Münzen, 40 (Basel December 13,
                            1969) 56, no. 93.

Dilute glaze: shading on the
                        helmets, hair, beards, leaves of the tree, and satyr tails and harnesses;
                        ornaments of the giant's belt and Dionysos' boots; pattern on the snake.

Rudolf Lepcke, Auktion 2035 (Berlin November 12, 1930)
